<TITLE> RAB raids city club for criminals </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Nov 1 (bdnews24.com)  The Rapid Action Battalion raided Fu-Wang Bowling Club in Gulshan late Thursday night in search of "criminals". A RAB officer, who did not want to be named, told bdnews24.com that the raid was part of a broader plan to "flush out criminals". bdnews24.com's correspondent Abu Noman Sajib saw a woman cry outside the club as the raid went on. The womanher name unknownarrived there with her daughter to take her son home from the club. Several other families were waiting outside. The crowd grew, with the time ticking away into early Friday morning. A security guard for Fu Wang, Akmal Hossain, said the RAB officers hemmed in the club at 11pm as the "disco" inside was pumping out loud music. Akmal said the officers locked the main gate to the club and then the "disco" before they herded the clubbers on the roof of the two-storey building. The RAB officers let go of those with drinking permits and held those without. RAB-1 operations officer Abul Hossain told bdnews24.com: "We have information that the city's clubs have become haunts of criminals." "It was a surprise raid on Fu Wang," he said, refusing to give further details on the raid. The bdnews24.com correspondent saw at least 10 "singers"three of them womenwalk out of the club into the road. At least four vehicles of RAB officers were parked on the road. Sajib saw up to seven women members of the elite-force inside one of the vehicles. bdn
